The paper discusses the concept of probabilities and their computation, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The mention of subjective degrees of belief suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), where probabilistic models are commonly used. The mention of marginal distributions suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT), where the study of probability distributions is a central topic. The mention of frequencies suggests a connection to statistical inference (cs.SI), where the estimation of probabilities from data is a common task. Finally, the mention of computation suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), where the efficient manipulation of probability distributions is an important problem.
